description:
A six issue mini-series that is a sequel to the Batman Season Two episodes "A Piece of the Action/Batman's Satisfaction" from March 1st and 2nd, 1967. The two-part episode featured The Green Hornet/Britt Reid (Van Williams) and Kato (Bruce Lee) visiting Gotham. They team up with Batman and Robin to face Colonel Gumm (Roger C. Carmel).

This sequel is written by Kevin Smith with Ralph Garman; penciled by Ty Templeton, with painted covers by Alex Ross.

The digital edition can be found here.

Collected in Batman '66 Meets the Green Hornet.
name: Batman '66 Meets the Green Hornet

description: Allowing Drew Friedman to indulge his fondness for wrinkles and liver spots to the hilt, this portrait gallery of Jewish comedians born before 1930 includes the famous (Milton Berle, George Burns, Groucho Marx, Jerry Lewis, Alan King, Mel Brooks, Buddy Hackett, Phil Silvers, Jack Benny, Henny Youngman), the not-so-famous (Irwin Corey, Benny Rubin, Shelly Berman, Shecky Greene) and the largely unknown (Al Kelly, Menasha Skulnik). Old Jewish Comedians traces a direct link not only to the traditions of vaudeville and burlesque but to the once-thriving international Yiddish theatre and culture. Featuring a fascinating historical introduction by none other than Leonard Maltin!-- publisher's website
name: Old Jewish Comedians: A Visual Encyclopedia
